

sudo su
yum install nginx -y
cd /usr/share/nginx/html
echo "<html><h1>Welcome to AWS Cloud</h1></html>" > index.html
service nginx start



Explanation:
sudo su: Switch to the root user.
yum install nginx -y: Installs the Nginx web server.
cd /usr/share/nginx/html: Navigate to the default document root directory for Nginx.
echo "<html><h1>Welcome to AWS Cloud</h1></html>" > index.html: Creates a simple HTML file as the static website's homepage.
service nginx start: Starts the Nginx web server.
Access Your Website:
Once you complete the above steps, open a browser and visit:

plaintext

http://your-ec2-public-ip
